    "input": {
      "base": "main",
      "body": "## Summary\n\nThis pull request adds a deployment-focused GitHub Actions workflow for the Node.js project. The workflow runs on pushes to `main` and creates a deployment tracking issue, prepares rollback artifacts, verifies artifact checksums, and closes the tracking issue once deployment status work completes.\n\n## Workflow overview\n\n- **pre-deployment**\n  - Checks out the repository with commit history for previous SHA detection.\n  - Installs dependencies with `npm ci`.\n  - Runs `npm run lint` and `npm test`.\n  - Captures the previous commit SHA, current commit SHA, and package version.\n  - Creates a deployment tracking issue with `deployment` and `in-progress` labels.\n  - Adds a comment containing `Pre-deployment checks completed`.\n\n- **rollback-preparation**\n  - Builds an executable rollback script with validation and error handling.\n  - Backs up `package.json`, `package-lock.json`, and environment templates.\n  - Creates a dependency verification script.\n  - Generates step-by-step rollback documentation.\n  - Produces a compressed rollback package with SHA256 checksums.\n  - Uploads rollback artifacts with 30-day retention.\n  - Comments on the deployment issue with rollback details, verification statuses, checksum, and quick rollback commands.\n\n- **post-deployment**\n  - Downloads and verifies rollback artifact checksums.\n  - Removes the `in-progress` label and adds `completed`.\n  - Posts `Deployment Completed Successfully` with rollback artifact details.\n  - Closes the deployment tracking issue.\n\n## Notes\n\n- The workflow uses `actions/github-script` for issue and label management without redeclaring the provided `github` client.\n- Jobs are sequential: `pre-deployment` → `rollback-preparation` → `post-deployment`.\n- The trigger is scoped to pushes on the `main` branch only.",
